      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/35/1",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : فِي رَجُلٍ رَهَنَ عِنْدَ رَجُلٍ رَهْناً فَضَاعَ اَلرَّهْنُ قَالَ \"هُوَ مِنْ مَالِ اَلرَّاهِنِ وَ يَرْتَجِعُ اَلْمُرْتَهَنُ عَلَيْهِ بِمَالِهِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4094 - Muhammad ibn Abi Umayr narrated from Jamil ibn Darraj, who said that Abu Abdullah (as) was asked about a man who gave collateral (rahn) to another man, but the collateral was lost.\nImam (as) said: \"It is the responsibility of the pledger (rahin), and the pledgee (murtahin) has the right to claim his money from him.\""
        ]
      }
    },
